1
00:00:00,960 --> 00:00:03,170
Previously on Fairy Tail:

2
00:00:03,170 --> 00:00:06,220
That reporter from the Weekly 
Sorcerer was pretty amazing.

3
00:00:06,220 --> 00:00:09,020
He completely ignored you, Lucy.

4
00:00:09,020 --> 00:00:09,860
Don't laugh!

5
00:00:09,860 --> 00:00:12,570
But the guild has finally calmed down.

6
00:00:12,570 --> 00:00:13,520
You think?

7
00:00:13,520 --> 00:00:14,790
Seems the same way to me.

8
00:00:14,790 --> 00:00:17,560
And Lucy ain't got a boyfriend as usual, too.

9
00:00:17,780 --> 00:00:20,040
Why are you talking about that again?!

10
00:01:52,820 --> 00:01:56,990
Today, as happens only occasionally, 
it is raining in Magnolia.

11
00:01:59,740 --> 00:02:01,660
And in a certain out of the 
way corner of the city,

12
00:02:01,660 --> 00:02:04,860
there is a suspicious-looking magic shop.

13
00:02:08,030 --> 00:02:09,490
Drip, drip, drop...

14
00:02:13,290 --> 00:02:17,510
So you want to get him to notice you, eh?

15
00:02:17,510 --> 00:02:20,860
Well, I have the perfect thing for that.

16
00:02:21,110 --> 00:02:24,700
All Juvia wants is for him 
to gaze in her direction.

17
00:02:27,150 --> 00:02:28,800
Drip, drip, drop.

18
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:32,320
Well, it's not beyond the 
ability of my potions.

19
00:02:32,320 --> 00:02:35,800
Here. Try using this.

20
00:02:35,800 --> 00:02:36,850
And this is?

21
00:02:36,850 --> 00:02:41,190
It's a potion that will get him 
to gaze at you passionately.

22
00:02:41,190 --> 00:02:42,930
60,000 jewel.

23
00:02:42,930 --> 00:02:43,960
That is quite expensive.

24
00:02:43,960 --> 00:02:46,940
If you try and haggle, then no sale.

25
00:02:46,940 --> 00:02:49,760
It is 100% effective, after all.

26
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:52,750
100%... Passionate gaze...

27
00:02:53,530 --> 00:02:55,200
I will pay it.

28
00:02:56,630 --> 00:02:58,210
Drip, drip, drop.

29
00:02:59,950 --> 00:03:04,650
This mysterious potion that 
Juvia bought at full price

30
00:03:04,650 --> 00:03:10,050
could well bring Fairy Tail 
to the brink of destruction.

31
00:03:10,050 --> 00:03:13,700
But no one is yet aware of the danger.

32
00:03:14,740 --> 00:03:18,570
Special Request: Watch 
Out for the Guy You Like!

33
00:03:23,820 --> 00:03:25,200
Nothing to do!

34
00:03:25,200 --> 00:03:27,400
Why don't you go on a job?

35
00:03:27,400 --> 00:03:31,180
Well, Natsu said he wanted 
to rest for a little while.

36
00:03:31,180 --> 00:03:35,190
Couldn't you go by yourself, 
or with some other people?

37
00:03:36,250 --> 00:03:40,290
But I have a responsibility to 
him since we're on the same team.

38
00:03:40,290 --> 00:03:42,480
You guys really get along well.

39
00:03:42,990 --> 00:03:44,630
Like you're a couple!

40
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:46,030
We are not!

41
00:03:46,680 --> 00:03:49,950
But Natsu might really love you, Lucy.

42
00:03:57,080 --> 00:04:00,440
Even if that's the case, I think I'll pass.

43
00:04:00,440 --> 00:04:02,740
I think you two would 
be a good match, though.

44
00:04:07,500 --> 00:04:10,890
Hey, Natsu! We'd better go 
on a job soon, or else...

45
00:04:10,890 --> 00:04:12,600
You, put on some clothes!

46
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:17,100
Did you use too much fire and turn 
your brain to charcoal, Natsu?

47
00:04:17,100 --> 00:04:21,150
Hey, give it a rest! You gotta take 
a day off once in a while, right?

48
00:04:21,150 --> 00:04:22,750
Isn't that right, Happy?

49
00:04:23,080 --> 00:04:24,300
Aye!

50
00:04:24,300 --> 00:04:25,710
Refresh!

51
00:04:25,710 --> 00:04:27,880
And to refresh, you do this!

52
00:04:32,370 --> 00:04:34,440
Yeah, I don't think so.

53
00:04:34,750 --> 00:04:37,250
I think you two would 
be a good match, though.

54
00:04:39,530 --> 00:04:40,930
Gray-sama...

55
00:04:40,930 --> 00:04:43,420
May your passionate gaze 
only be aimed at Juvia!

56
00:04:44,290 --> 00:04:46,540
Ah, this is so nerve-wracking!

57
00:04:47,110 --> 00:04:50,220
Even Juvia's hands are shaking!

58
00:04:50,700 --> 00:04:51,680
No!

59
00:04:52,180 --> 00:04:54,800
I think you two would make 
a good couple, though.

60
00:04:55,190 --> 00:04:56,780
Not a chance.

61
00:04:57,020 --> 00:05:00,740
Sheesh, Mira-san. Don't even joke about that.

62
00:05:01,930 --> 00:05:04,360
That's dangerous, Lucy-chan!

63
00:05:05,490 --> 00:05:06,900
I'm home!

64
00:05:06,900 --> 00:05:07,700
...says me.

65
00:05:07,940 --> 00:05:08,800
Yo!

66
00:05:08,800 --> 00:05:10,450
Letting yourself in again?!

67
00:05:10,700 --> 00:05:13,590
Actually, I have something 
important to ask you.

68
00:05:13,840 --> 00:05:17,640
Man, you really love my house, you know that?

69
00:05:15,960 --> 00:05:16,410
Love

70
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:21,020
Love!!?

71
00:05:19,420 --> 00:05:20,340
Love.

72
00:05:21,020 --> 00:05:24,200
Natsu might really love you, Lucy.

73
00:05:32,680 --> 00:05:33,810
Go home!

74
00:05:34,560 --> 00:05:36,310
But it's important.

75
00:05:36,790 --> 00:05:38,060
Talk about something important

76
00:05:36,790 --> 00:05:38,390
Important?

77
00:05:38,390 --> 00:05:39,940
Go home!

78
00:05:41,130 --> 00:05:42,570
What's with you?

79
00:05:42,570 --> 00:05:44,220
Somebody's in a lousy mood today!

80
00:05:44,220 --> 00:05:45,900
Leave using the door!

81
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:55,340
Crap... What's going on here?

82
00:05:56,480 --> 00:05:58,100
The next day.

83
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:03,000
Nothing to do...

84
00:06:03,540 --> 00:06:04,920
Hey there!

85
00:06:05,170 --> 00:06:07,020
You feelin' better?

86
00:06:07,020 --> 00:06:09,880
Get off! Stop being all over me like that!

87
00:06:10,830 --> 00:06:12,440
Hey, Lucy...

88
00:06:12,440 --> 00:06:14,800
This is bad. This is real bad.

89
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:17,380
I'm being totally self conscious...

90
00:06:17,380 --> 00:06:18,730
Natsu!

91
00:06:18,730 --> 00:06:20,150
That's about enough!

92
00:06:20,150 --> 00:06:22,330
How long are you planning on playing around?

93
00:06:22,330 --> 00:06:23,980
What's that?

94
00:06:23,980 --> 00:06:25,150
You wanna go, buddy?

95
00:06:25,150 --> 00:06:26,960
Fight!

96
00:06:28,100 --> 00:06:29,570
Gray-sama...

97
00:06:29,860 --> 00:06:32,950
Yesterday, Juvia was too 
nervous, she couldn't...

98
00:06:33,220 --> 00:06:36,230
But today, Juvia has made up her mind!

99
00:06:37,840 --> 00:06:39,980
What type of potion is this?

100
00:06:40,780 --> 00:06:44,000
Blow on the contents of the flask,

101
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:47,520
and have the person you are interested 
in swallow just a little.

102
00:06:47,520 --> 00:06:52,970
If you do, your passionate feelings will 
reach them, perhaps. That's how it works.

103
00:06:58,090 --> 00:06:59,350
Gray-sama...

104
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:03,130
This passion burning within, growing stronger 
and stronger as long as you are out of reach...

105
00:07:03,130 --> 00:07:04,000
Love!

106
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:07,940
The closer Juvia gets, the 
more impatient she feels!

107
00:07:08,360 --> 00:07:11,630
But today, that will all be over.

108
00:07:11,630 --> 00:07:16,490
Starting today, Juvia and Gray-sama 
will be together as one, as lovers!

109
00:07:16,740 --> 00:07:18,580
Oh, my!

110
00:07:19,810 --> 00:07:22,440
Oh, right! I don't have time for this!

111
00:07:22,440 --> 00:07:24,200
What's that supposed to mean?

112
00:07:24,200 --> 00:07:27,750
It seems like Natsu has some 
girl he's in love with.

113
00:07:28,040 --> 00:07:29,250
You mean our Natsu?

114
00:07:29,250 --> 00:07:30,530
No way.

115
00:07:30,530 --> 00:07:31,710
What a laugh.

116
00:07:31,710 --> 00:07:35,220
That's the last thing I'd 
expect to hear about him.

117
00:07:35,470 --> 00:07:36,930
It's the truth!

118
00:07:36,930 --> 00:07:40,560
Lately he's been all "I want 
to see her, I want to see her!"

119
00:07:40,560 --> 00:07:41,290
See who?

120
00:07:41,290 --> 00:07:42,440
I don't know.

121
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:44,300
What'll I do? What'll I do?

122
00:07:44,300 --> 00:07:46,340
It's me!

123
00:07:46,340 --> 00:07:48,250
It's not like I hate him or anything...

124
00:07:48,250 --> 00:07:51,300
When it comes to love or 
dating, well, it's just...

125
00:07:51,300 --> 00:07:55,070
I've never gone out with a guy before!

126
00:07:57,300 --> 00:07:58,360
I want to see you.

127
00:07:59,380 --> 00:08:02,300
Stop prettifying him, Lucy!

128
00:08:04,540 --> 00:08:07,820
Stop getting wild ideas, Lucy!

129
00:08:08,140 --> 00:08:09,250
Hey, Lucy...

130
00:08:12,950 --> 00:08:14,090
Yes?

131
00:08:14,490 --> 00:08:17,600
Tonight, I have something important 
to talk with you about.

132
00:08:20,590 --> 00:08:23,720
Would you come by the Sola tree 
in the South Gate Park tonight?

133
00:08:24,650 --> 00:08:25,770
Why?

134
00:08:26,690 --> 00:08:28,390
I have something important to talk about.

135
00:08:29,100 --> 00:08:30,920
Make sure you come alone.

136
00:08:31,250 --> 00:08:32,490
He's blushing?

137
00:08:32,490 --> 00:08:33,640
Blushing?

138
00:08:34,300 --> 00:08:36,410
Natsu blushed!

139
00:08:36,410 --> 00:08:37,500
Later!

140
00:08:39,450 --> 00:08:40,820
Mira-san...

141
00:08:41,600 --> 00:08:44,300
I'm going home for the day.

142
00:08:44,830 --> 00:08:47,700
Natsu! Where the hell do 
you think you're going?

143
00:08:47,700 --> 00:08:50,690
Now, Gray-sama... Your passionate gaze!

144
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:54,470
That bastard... Wait, Natsu!

145
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:01,600
Look at Juvia!

146
00:09:11,850 --> 00:09:14,470
Stop moving, Gray-sama!

147
00:09:14,470 --> 00:09:17,550
At this rate, everyone is going to be 
looking at Juvia passionately!

148
00:09:17,550 --> 00:09:19,120
No one needs that!

149
00:09:19,240 --> 00:09:22,580
Gray-sama!

150
00:09:27,120 --> 00:09:28,250
I did it!

151
00:09:35,860 --> 00:09:37,920
What is this feeling?

152
00:09:39,190 --> 00:09:41,600
Finally... Finally...

153
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:44,470
Ah! Gray-sama's...

154
00:09:44,720 --> 00:09:49,130
...passionate gaze...

155
00:09:54,570 --> 00:09:55,820
You're always...

156
00:09:56,110 --> 00:09:59,660
You're always flying as you 
damn well please in the sky!

157
00:09:59,660 --> 00:10:00,410
What?

158
00:10:00,650 --> 00:10:03,110
I'm strong, but I can't fly!

159
00:10:03,110 --> 00:10:05,400
You're weak, but you can fly!

160
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:07,160
So in the end, we're even!

161
00:10:07,410 --> 00:10:08,800
Happy!

162
00:10:08,800 --> 00:10:11,830
You are my rival!

163
00:10:12,710 --> 00:10:14,710
What are you talking about, Gray?

164
00:10:14,710 --> 00:10:16,950
I challenge you, Happy!

165
00:10:16,950 --> 00:10:20,690
Natsu, I'm scared! Gray's acting all freaky!

166
00:10:20,690 --> 00:10:22,450
Where's Natsu?

167
00:10:22,450 --> 00:10:25,520
N-No... Where's the passionate gaze?

168
00:10:27,430 --> 00:10:30,430
Wakaba, how much you make last month?

169
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:33,110
A lot more than you, I bet!

170
00:10:33,110 --> 00:10:35,660
There's no way I could lose to you!

171
00:10:35,660 --> 00:10:38,190
You, especially, I won't lose to!

172
00:10:38,440 --> 00:10:41,430
What are we to each other, again?

173
00:10:41,430 --> 00:10:44,660
Rivals, of course! That's how it should be!

174
00:10:45,890 --> 00:10:48,750
Drink alcohol, but don't be drowned by it!

175
00:10:48,750 --> 00:10:49,900
You listening, alcohol?

176
00:10:49,900 --> 00:10:52,660
I ain't gonna lose to the likes of you!

177
00:10:52,660 --> 00:10:55,140
It is you that is my fated rival!

178
00:10:55,140 --> 00:10:58,350
What do you mean, your 
rival is alcohol, Master?

179
00:10:58,350 --> 00:11:01,710
Alcohol isn't a person. 
It can't be your rival.

180
00:11:01,710 --> 00:11:04,640
I won't be drowned! I 
won't be drowned in you!

181
00:11:04,640 --> 00:11:05,600
We battle!

182
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:09,040
You, pillar over there!

183
00:11:09,040 --> 00:11:11,450
Why must you always obstruct my path?

184
00:11:11,450 --> 00:11:14,400
All I ever wished for was to 
pass through here, unhindered,

185
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:15,360
and yet, why?!

186
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:17,800
Why must you challenge me so?

187
00:11:17,800 --> 00:11:20,640
Do you intend to make me your rival?

188
00:11:20,640 --> 00:11:22,840
Uh, being rivals with a pillar is...

189
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:24,440
That's just not happening.

190
00:11:24,440 --> 00:11:28,150
Alcohol is one thing, but a 
pillar is right out there.

191
00:11:28,150 --> 00:11:31,250
Well, maybe if it pilloried her...

192
00:11:31,250 --> 00:11:32,960
I'll just let that sit there.

193
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:36,450
Erza! Let's fight like we 
used to back in the day!

194
00:11:36,450 --> 00:11:38,180
I'm not gonna lose, no way!

195
00:11:38,180 --> 00:11:41,010
Because you are my lifelong rival, Erza!

196
00:11:41,250 --> 00:11:43,800
Hey, what's going on?

197
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:45,390
Where are you, Natsu?

198
00:11:45,390 --> 00:11:48,500
I challenge you, Happy!

199
00:11:48,500 --> 00:11:50,000
Now look here.

200
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:52,620
I am going to fly farther 
than you, without fail!

201
00:11:52,620 --> 00:11:54,150
It's impossible, I say!

202
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:56,310
No! I will fly!

203
00:11:56,310 --> 00:11:59,900
Against you... Against my rival...

204
00:12:00,030 --> 00:12:02,790
I will not lose, no matter what!

205
00:12:02,790 --> 00:12:05,780
Where'd you go, Natsu?!

206
00:12:06,360 --> 00:12:10,700
Could it be that it takes some time 
before the potion takes effect?

207
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:14,620
I think an explanation is in order.

208
00:12:16,540 --> 00:12:22,450
That's something I mixed up with a 
bunch of forbidden magical ingredients.

209
00:12:22,450 --> 00:12:25,600
Who knows what effect it might have?

210
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:28,590
And why would I do such a thing?

211
00:12:28,590 --> 00:12:31,370
Because I needed some cash to make a getaway!

212
00:12:31,700 --> 00:12:33,390
And there you have it.

213
00:12:33,390 --> 00:12:35,980
What will become of Fairy Tail?

214
00:12:47,530 --> 00:12:49,580
What'll I do? What'll I do?

215
00:12:49,580 --> 00:12:52,580
Would you come by the Sola tree 
in the South Gate Park tonight?

216
00:12:53,150 --> 00:12:54,950
I have something important to talk about.

217
00:12:54,950 --> 00:12:56,150
Make sure you come alone.

218
00:12:57,060 --> 00:12:58,660
What'll I do? What'll I do?

219
00:12:58,660 --> 00:13:01,670
This has got to be a love 
confession! Definitely!

220
00:13:02,650 --> 00:13:04,230
I have to turn him down...

221
00:13:04,230 --> 00:13:07,130
After all, we're on the same team...

222
00:13:07,730 --> 00:13:09,870
I'm sorry, Natsu...

223
00:13:11,380 --> 00:13:13,930
This is the perfect chance to wear that!

224
00:13:14,360 --> 00:13:16,570
Yup, this will work great!

225
00:13:16,570 --> 00:13:19,440
Wait.  This is all wrong!

226
00:13:19,700 --> 00:13:22,450
Idiot! What the heck are you thinking, Lucy?!

227
00:13:22,450 --> 00:13:24,290
I mean, what'll I do? What'll I do?

228
00:13:24,290 --> 00:13:25,790
Oh, I know!

229
00:13:25,790 --> 00:13:29,130
Gate of the Giant Crab, I open thee! Cancer!

230
00:13:30,100 --> 00:13:31,220
Cancer.

231
00:13:31,700 --> 00:13:33,410
Make me look cute, 'kay?

232
00:13:33,410 --> 00:13:34,580
As you wish-ebi.

233
00:13:34,580 --> 00:13:37,390
What the hell are you doing, Lucy?

234
00:13:37,390 --> 00:13:40,410
And yet, I ended up doing it myself!

235
00:13:50,700 --> 00:13:53,100
Iron Fist of the Fire Dragon...

236
00:13:53,740 --> 00:13:56,520
Let's have 30 babies together, Lucy.

237
00:13:56,520 --> 00:13:57,380
Sure!

238
00:14:00,500 --> 00:14:02,120
I'm all fired up.

239
00:14:05,700 --> 00:14:07,810
I'm saying that's not how it is!

240
00:14:07,810 --> 00:14:10,000
And why were they Happys?

241
00:14:11,030 --> 00:14:13,080
Master!

242
00:14:13,080 --> 00:14:14,730
Let's have a drinking contest!

243
00:14:14,730 --> 00:14:17,550
I always wanted to challenge you!

244
00:14:17,550 --> 00:14:19,880
You are not my rival!

245
00:14:19,880 --> 00:14:21,550
My rival is alcohol itself!

246
00:14:21,550 --> 00:14:23,000
I won't lose!

247
00:14:23,710 --> 00:14:25,600
Three against three.

248
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:29,720
Don't go thinking that just because we're 
equal in number, we're equal in ability.

249
00:14:30,290 --> 00:14:34,670
When you talk about teams of three 
in Fairy Tail, it always means us!

250
00:14:34,670 --> 00:14:35,600
Let's battle!

251
00:14:35,850 --> 00:14:38,840
Is there no real Man here?

252
00:14:38,840 --> 00:14:41,020
If there's a rival for me, show yourself!

253
00:14:41,020 --> 00:14:45,680
I am saddened! I am violently saddened!

254
00:14:43,260 --> 00:14:46,700
Ah, so he thinks he has no rival.

255
00:14:46,700 --> 00:14:48,770
Where does he get that self-confidence from?

256
00:14:48,770 --> 00:14:50,530
You finished adding it up, rival?

257
00:14:50,780 --> 00:14:54,530
Of course! And faster than you, rival!

258
00:14:55,300 --> 00:14:57,370
Getting a little dull in the tooth, I see.

259
00:14:57,620 --> 00:15:00,400
D-Damn you! I'm...

260
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:01,890
On the count of three.

261
00:15:01,890 --> 00:15:02,940
Bring it on!

262
00:15:02,940 --> 00:15:05,140
The amount of money I made last month is...

263
00:15:05,140 --> 00:15:06,150
One, two...

264
00:15:06,150 --> 00:15:08,000
150,000 jewel all in all!

265
00:15:09,310 --> 00:15:11,130
The same?

266
00:15:11,130 --> 00:15:13,080
Then we'll do battle with 
the month before last!

267
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:15,610
We Raijin Tribe versus you Shadow Gear!

268
00:15:15,610 --> 00:15:19,770
We'll decide just who is the best 
three-person team in Fairy Tail!

269
00:15:19,770 --> 00:15:23,350
Don't be surprised when you see our skills!

270
00:15:23,350 --> 00:15:24,410
Damn you...

271
00:15:24,410 --> 00:15:26,470


272
00:15:26,470 --> 00:15:28,400
They're having a posing competition?

273
00:15:28,750 --> 00:15:29,950
Not yet!

274
00:15:29,950 --> 00:15:31,260
Not yet!

275
00:15:31,260 --> 00:15:33,410
Where is a Man?

276
00:15:37,340 --> 00:15:39,600
Lucy-chan, that's dangerous!

277
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:41,040
I'll be fine!

278
00:15:41,040 --> 00:15:43,350
Well, aren't you lookin' good today!

279
00:15:43,350 --> 00:15:46,240
Don't go fallin' in the 
river before your date!

280
00:15:46,880 --> 00:15:49,030
D-Date?

281
00:15:54,110 --> 00:15:57,290
Good. At least I look cute.

282
00:15:58,100 --> 00:15:59,310
I mean, this is all wrong!

283
00:15:59,310 --> 00:16:01,770
All wrong! All wrong!

284
00:16:10,590 --> 00:16:14,100
This is not gonna work! We're co-workers!

285
00:16:14,100 --> 00:16:17,740
I'll be together with Natsu for...

286
00:16:18,640 --> 00:16:21,610
We'll be together forever, Lucy.

287
00:16:21,610 --> 00:16:23,290
Together forever?

288
00:16:25,040 --> 00:16:26,330
Requip!

289
00:16:26,330 --> 00:16:27,960
Heaven's Wheel Armor!

290
00:16:30,910 --> 00:16:32,370
Erza, stop this!

291
00:16:32,370 --> 00:16:35,550
We just rebuilt the place! 
Don't go destroying it!

292
00:16:35,550 --> 00:16:36,630
Silence!

293
00:16:36,630 --> 00:16:39,370
This guy is constantly standing up in my way!

294
00:16:39,370 --> 00:16:42,440
It especially makes me angry when I wish 
to go further inside without delay!

295
00:16:42,440 --> 00:16:46,100
It's impossible to go further 
in without going around it!

296
00:16:46,100 --> 00:16:49,360
It is this pillar that is 
always standing in my way,

297
00:16:49,360 --> 00:16:51,220
in other words, my rival!

298
00:16:51,220 --> 00:16:53,690
Yeah, but you just have to 
go around it a little...

299
00:16:53,690 --> 00:16:55,820
I know you like to take things 
straight on, but sheesh...

300
00:16:56,070 --> 00:16:59,410
Erza tends not to look where she's going.

301
00:16:59,410 --> 00:17:00,410
That's not true.

302
00:17:00,720 --> 00:17:03,050
Erza, fight me!

303
00:17:03,050 --> 00:17:04,900
Your rival is right here!

304
00:17:04,900 --> 00:17:08,400
I'm facing down my lifelong rival right now!

305
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:11,200
Uh, it's just a pillar.

306
00:17:12,070 --> 00:17:14,040
I can't believe this!

307
00:17:14,040 --> 00:17:15,800
Satan Soul!

308
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:17,460
Stop it, already!

309
00:17:17,460 --> 00:17:20,010
Requip! Purgatory Armor!

310
00:17:20,010 --> 00:17:22,060
Listen, just stop, already!

311
00:17:22,060 --> 00:17:27,350
Wildcat... Punch!

312
00:17:27,350 --> 00:17:31,150
Where's a real Man?

313
00:17:31,150 --> 00:17:32,700
Punch!

314
00:17:33,270 --> 00:17:34,430
It's no use.

315
00:17:34,430 --> 00:17:37,110
The guild's gonna be destroyed again...

316
00:17:38,970 --> 00:17:39,780
And?

317
00:17:40,650 --> 00:17:44,200
Gray, it's impossible, I tell you! Stop this!

318
00:17:44,470 --> 00:17:45,710
That's no good!

319
00:17:45,710 --> 00:17:48,690
I am going to surpass you, my rival!

320
00:17:48,690 --> 00:17:50,550
Juvia is so vexed!

321
00:17:50,550 --> 00:17:51,960
More potion...

322
00:17:53,080 --> 00:17:56,190
Come, my rival! Follow me!

323
00:18:00,400 --> 00:18:01,220
Gray!

324
00:18:04,260 --> 00:18:07,470
I'm even more fired up!

325
00:18:07,470 --> 00:18:09,900
He's all like Natsu!

326
00:18:09,900 --> 00:18:12,020
I will fly!

327
00:18:18,490 --> 00:18:22,950
I will fly!

328
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:23,920


329
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:27,690
Fly, me!

330
00:18:29,050 --> 00:18:32,140
The Sola tree in South Gate Park.

331
00:18:34,930 --> 00:18:36,370
Keep it together...

332
00:18:36,370 --> 00:18:39,600
Keep it together... Stay calm, Lucy!

333
00:18:40,790 --> 00:18:42,480
Hey, Lucy!

334
00:18:43,910 --> 00:18:46,580
What'll I do? What'll I do?

335
00:18:49,200 --> 00:18:52,830
I'm a pushover when it comes to pushy people!

336
00:18:55,320 --> 00:18:58,690
You're late! Out with that 
maid of yours already.

337
00:18:59,630 --> 00:19:01,130
What was her name again?

338
00:19:01,130 --> 00:19:03,530
You know... Right, Virgo.

339
00:19:04,030 --> 00:19:06,540
The ground's really hard here.

340
00:19:06,540 --> 00:19:09,150
I'll never be able to dig it up 
without that Spirit maid of yours.

341
00:19:10,090 --> 00:19:11,330
Uh, um...

342
00:19:12,140 --> 00:19:14,950
And the important thing 
you wanted to talk about?

343
00:19:16,540 --> 00:19:19,580
I hear there's a treasure buried here!

344
00:19:19,580 --> 00:19:24,650
It's supposed to be an album of embarrassing 
pictures of everyone in Fairy Tail!

345
00:19:24,650 --> 00:19:27,040
Gramps hid it here a long time ago, I heard!

346
00:19:27,040 --> 00:19:29,180
Isn't this gonna be fun?

347
00:19:30,120 --> 00:19:34,310
And...the girl you fell 
in love with recently?

348
00:19:34,310 --> 00:19:35,820
What? Huh?

349
00:19:35,820 --> 00:19:38,400
You were saying "I want to 
see her, I want to see her."

350
00:19:38,400 --> 00:19:38,980
Oh.

351
00:19:39,500 --> 00:19:43,340
It's not like I care one way 
or the other, but it was Virgo.

352
00:19:43,340 --> 00:19:46,400
I was hoping she'd dig the hole for me!

353
00:19:47,040 --> 00:19:48,990
The hole?

354
00:19:48,990 --> 00:19:50,250
The hole?

355
00:19:50,570 --> 00:19:51,620
The hole?!

356
00:20:00,470 --> 00:20:05,150
I am such a total fool!

357
00:20:05,150 --> 00:20:09,370
And, just like the previous episode, 
Lucy is disappointed in the end.

358
00:20:14,930 --> 00:20:17,520
What in the world happened?

359
00:20:20,610 --> 00:20:22,610
Thank goodness...

360
00:20:24,970 --> 00:20:29,570
Gray, hang in there! It's 
morning already, Gray!

361
00:20:32,810 --> 00:20:35,950
Juvia! You came to save him, right?

362
00:20:35,950 --> 00:20:37,370
Gray-sama...

363
00:20:37,370 --> 00:20:38,760
So sorry!

364
00:20:38,760 --> 00:20:40,750
To make you go through all that...

365
00:20:41,650 --> 00:20:44,630
The reason the potion
didn't work correctly is surely

366
00:20:44,630 --> 00:20:47,770
because Juvia's feelings
for you weren't strong enough!

367
00:20:55,400 --> 00:20:56,650
Gray-sama!

368
00:20:57,690 --> 00:21:00,700
Juvia? What happened to me?

369
00:21:00,700 --> 00:21:02,600
You're safe... Thank goodness.

370
00:21:02,850 --> 00:21:04,930
She lllikes you!

371
00:21:04,930 --> 00:21:07,620
I knew I was cold for some reason.

372
00:21:07,620 --> 00:21:09,940
Stop gettin' me all soaked.

373
00:21:09,940 --> 00:21:11,190
How many times do I have to tell you?

374
00:21:13,070 --> 00:21:15,610
No! Juvia is shocked!

375
00:21:15,610 --> 00:21:17,470
Huh? What is it?

376
00:21:17,470 --> 00:21:19,500
It isn't enough, it just isn't!

377
00:21:19,500 --> 00:21:21,690
And that's why Juvia...

378
00:21:21,960 --> 00:21:24,280
is breakin' out the potion!

379
00:21:31,250 --> 00:21:32,880
Juvia is over here!

380
00:21:32,880 --> 00:21:35,020
You! Horizon over there!

381
00:21:35,050 --> 00:21:38,720
You are my rival!

382
00:21:39,250 --> 00:21:41,000
Gray-sama!

383
00:21:41,000 --> 00:21:42,290
Wait!

384
00:21:42,290 --> 00:21:45,340
I guess some people weren't meant to fly.

385
00:21:45,340 --> 00:21:49,700
And, just like Lucy, Juvia 
is disappointed in the end.

386
00:21:50,950 --> 00:21:53,220
A few days later...

387
00:21:54,790 --> 00:21:56,400
Nothing to do...

388
00:21:56,400 --> 00:21:57,720
Hey, Lucy.

389
00:21:57,720 --> 00:21:58,980
Yes?

390
00:21:58,980 --> 00:22:01,250
I was just thinking...

391
00:22:01,620 --> 00:22:05,540
Don't you think Gray loves you, Lucy?

392
00:22:06,590 --> 00:22:10,100
Please, just leave me alone!

393
00:22:11,710 --> 00:22:16,680
What? A spell to make feelings 
mutual? Doesn't exist.

394
00:22:17,280 --> 00:22:18,850
Wait...

395
00:22:18,850 --> 00:22:21,550
Why did I end up here?

396
00:22:21,550 --> 00:22:24,230
It's the Curse of the Moon!

397
00:23:55,940 --> 00:23:59,200
What? Some guys from a Dark 
Guild are runnin' amok?

398
00:23:59,200 --> 00:24:02,190
All righty! I'll go and bust 'em up!

399
00:24:02,190 --> 00:24:04,510
You can't! They've got hostages.

400
00:24:04,510 --> 00:24:07,130
I bet you'd beat the hostages 
up with them, Natsu.

401
00:24:07,130 --> 00:24:09,030
Even so, I'll do it!

402
00:24:09,030 --> 00:24:10,520
I said no, and that's it!

403
00:24:10,520 --> 00:24:13,260
Then at least give me more screen time!

404
00:24:13,500 --> 00:24:16,260
Next time: Love & Lucky!

405
00:24:16,260 --> 00:24:18,360
Huh? Is that why?

406
00:24:18,360 --> 00:24:21,390
Well, don't you get the feeling 
I haven't shown up much lately?

407
00:24:21,640 --> 00:24:23,980
Life ain't all roses, you know.

408
00:24:23,980 --> 00:24:26,230


